{# Page header #}
<div class="bg-ebcu-blue pt-24 pb-12">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white">Ordering beer in bars and restaurants</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-white/90 max-w-2xl">
      In the on-trade, you don't always see the label. Here's how to get the information you need.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
  <div class="rounded-xl border border-ebcu-blue bg-ebcu-blue-light p-6 mb-12">
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      <span class="font-semibold">Your rights:</span> Staff must be able to provide allergen information for any product on request.
      This is required by EU food law.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-12">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Questions you can ask</h2>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 shadow-sm p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-lg mb-4">Before ordering</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded border-2 border-gray-300 mt-0.5"></div>
              <span class="text-gray-600">"Can I see the bottle or can?" (for packaged beers)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded border-2 border-gray-300 mt-0.5"></div>
              <span class="text-gray-600">"Where is this beer brewed?"</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded border-2 border-gray-300 mt-0.5"></div>
              <span class="text-gray-600">"Does this contain [specific allergen]?"</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded border-2 border-gray-300 mt-0.5"></div>
              <span class="text-gray-600">"Is this the same beer as [brand], or a different brewery?"</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded border-2 border-gray-300 mt-0.5"></div>
              <span class="text-gray-600">"How fresh is this?" (especially for hoppy beers)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 shadow-sm p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-lg mb-4">For draught beer</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded border-2 border-gray-300 mt-0.5"></div>
              <span class="text-gray-600">"When was this keg tapped?"</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded border-2 border-gray-300 mt-0.5"></div>
              <span class="text-gray-600">"Is this cask or keg conditioned?"</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded border-2 border-gray-300 mt-0.5"></div>
              <span class="text-gray-600">"What gas is this served with?" (CO2, nitrogen, mixed, or natural)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What to look for</h2>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 shadow-sm p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Good signs</h3>
          <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>Staff can answer questions about the beer</li>
            <li>Allergen information is available</li>
            <li>They can show you the packaging on request</li>
            <li>Tap handles match what's being poured</li>
            <li>Beer menu includes brewery/origin info</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 shadow-sm p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Worth questioning</h3>
          <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>Staff don't know where beer is brewed</li>
            <li>Can't provide allergen information</li>
            <li>Generic descriptions only ("it's a lager")</li>
            <li>Unwilling to show packaging</li>
            <li>Tap handle doesn't match the keg</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Related topics</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <a class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 shadow-sm p-5 hover:border-ebcu-blue hover:shadow-md transition-all" href="/topics/ingredients-allergens/">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Ingredients & allergens</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">What you can expect to find out about what's in your beer.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 shadow-sm p-5 hover:border-ebcu-blue hover:shadow-md transition-all" href="/topics/who-made-it/">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Who made this beer?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">How to find out who actually brewed what you're drinking.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
